JsFormbuilder
=============

Introduction goes here.

Example
=======

Rails => 
<% js_form_for :user, @user, :align => "vertical" do |f| %>
	<%= f.text_field :email %>
	<%= f.text_field :name %>
	<%= f.password_field :password %>
	<%= f.submit_or_cancel %>
<% end %>

HTML => 
<form action="/" class="vertical" method="post">
  <div class="row required">
    <div class="label">
      <label for="user_email">Email</label>
      <em>required</em></div>
    <div class="input">
      <div class="text_field">
        <input id="user_email" name="user[email]" size="30" type="text" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row required">
    <div class="label">
      <label for="user_name">Navn</label>
      <em>required</em></div>
    <div class="input">
      <div class="text_field">
        <input id="user_name" name="user[name]" size="30" type="text" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row required">
    <div class="label">
      <label for="user_password">Adgangskode</label>
      <em>required</em></div>
    <div class="input">
      <div class="password_field">
        <input id="user_password" name="user[password]" size="30" type="password" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="submit">
    <div class="submit_or_cancel">
      <input id="user_submit" name="commit" type="submit" value="Save changes" />
      or <a href="/">Cancel</a></div>
  </div>
</form>


The form builder handles translation as follows.

1. first it search for :label hash key.
f.text_field :name, :label => "Name"
2. it then tries to find inside locales
Class.human_attribute_name(method_name)
3. last it use the method_name :name and convert it to string.

Install
=======

First, to get the required options to work with the validations, you need to install validation_reflection plugin which add two methods reflect_on_all_validations and reflect_on_validations_for(:property) to the ActionRecord objects.

1. ruby script/plugin install git://github.com/redinger/validation_reflection.git

Next you just need to obtain the plugin itself.

2. ruby script/plugin install git://github.com/jamalsoueidan/js_formbuilder.git

You also need the stylesheet file form.css

3. rake js_formbuilder:install

Then open your layout file and put this code in the header.

<%= stylesheet_link_tag "form" %>
That's it :)

